Great Hearts Academies plans to extend spring break at all of our campuses through the week of March 16th. There will be no regular school or after-school activities during this week. We plan to resume classes on March 23, 2020. You can stay informed on our website: https://www.greatheartsamerica.org/coronavirus/

Should we need to extend again, we will tell you as soon as we have made that decision.

We are very sorry for the inconveniences and hardships this may cause, but we sincerely believe it is in the best interest of our community at this time.

ONLY 2 DAYS LEFT!

You only have until Sunday at midnight!

Simplify Teacher Gift-Giving = SNOWSTORM! ‚òÉÔ∏è‚ùÑÔ∏è
If you've been on campus lately, you may have noticed the flurry of snowflakes on the windows, doors, and hanging from the ceiling! Do you know what that means? It means it's time for our annual Chandler Prep Snowstorm! It's a way to show our amazing teachers how much we appreciate them through monetary gifts during the holiday season. Our teachers really look forward to and are so grateful for this flurry of appreciation. Take part in this wonderful CPA tradition.
You can donate in 2 ways: Go to the PSO website and click on the Snowstorm Link or send a check/cash to CPA PSO and turn it in to the PSO mailbox in the forum.

Happy Snowstorm!

post_text:
üí°SENIOR SPOTLIGHT: Isabelle Kelsey traveled alone to Thailand for an 18-day Elephant Conservation Service trip. She stayed in host communities and volunteered at 5 different elephant sanctuaries while visiting Chiang Mai, Bangkok, and Kanchanaburi, where she was education about human-elephant conflict and finding ways to create a peaceful coexistence through community-based conversation. She also helped with reforestation efforts and increased biodiversity in areas by planting trees, helped build a check dam which provides water for elephants, and visited elementary schools where she taught English to the younger students.

"I met amazing, passionate people on this trip. I also learned the importance of community and the role it plays in nature conservation, reforestation efforts, and creating peaceful coexistence between humans and elephants. I now realize that I want to have a bigger impact on the world."

post_text:
Emma Norton receives Girl Scouts Gold Award Recipient
Assists with National Park Service Project. With Emma‚Äôs love of nature and the outdoors, she has always felt that visitors have a responsibility to help protect the Canyon wildlife to assure the safety of all who visit the Grand Canyon.

Emma Worked closely with one of the committed Park rangers who helped Emma raised thousands of dollars for her project which allowed them to not only reprint instructions for the visitors and refurbish the food storage boxes but to actually replace all of the old and worn out containers with brand new ones. The new boxes were then installed in three different camp grounds (Bright Angel, Indian Garden and Cottonwood Campgrounds)within the canyon. Emma‚Äôs project and hard work will help minimize the human impact on the environment around the campgrounds for years to come.

As a result of her efforts and contribution to the Grand Canyon, Emma was awarded the Girl Scout Gold Award. Congratulation Emma! We are proud of you.

One of Alyssa‚Äôs greatest passions is fostering kittens for the Arizona Humane Society (AHS). This passion guided her in developing her project for her Girl Scouts Gold Award.

Alyssa identified ways to improve communication between the AHS staff, volunteers, and foster families. This included developing instructions, information packets and putting her artistic talent to work.

Alyssa designed, built and painted an organizational cubby for the AHS so foster families can easily get all the necessary materials needed when they pick up their foster animal. Congratulations to Alyssa Fink on her Girl Scout Gold Award! We are very proud of you and thank you for all that you have given back to CPA.

Chandler Prep Senior, Maddie Olsen, signed her Division II Athletic Letter of Intent to become a member of the Gannon University, Women‚Äôs Gymnastics Team.

Maddie is an honor student and has been an integral member of Desert Lights Gymnastics Team for many years. Maddie is also active in our Women‚Äôs Choir, Girl Up-empowering young women through advocacy programs and has volunteered in the Buddy Program where she works with Autistic Students.

Of our 18 CPA Collegiate athletes since 2010, Maddie is one of 9 CPA young women to become college athletes and the first Lady Titan to sign a Division II Letter. CPA happily celebrate; 1 Division I, 1 Division II, 3 NAIA, and 13 Division III Collegiate Athletes. Congratulations Maddie. Your hard work and sacrifice have paid off. We are all proud of you!

post_text: Emily Michael (Class of 2012) recently joined our students at Chandler Prep to discuss her current work in the Peace Corps. After graduating from The University of Arizona in 2016 she joined the Peace Corps. Emily is an Education Volunteer in Uganda, serving as a Literacy Specialist at a primary school in Arua, West Nile region. Besides working with teachers and pupils to improve reading, Emily is an advocate and trainer for sexual harassment support and an organizer for HIV interventions both in Arua and across Uganda. She has one more year in Peace Corps working with Catholic Relief Services, where her focus will be supporting a dedicated team improving health outcomes for orphans and vulnerable children.

Simplify Teacher Gift-Giving = SNOWSTORM!‚ùÑÔ∏è‚òÉÔ∏è‚ùÑÔ∏è

If you've been on campus lately, you may have noticed the flurry of snowflakes on the windows, doors, and hanging from the ceiling!

Our teachers really look forward to and are so grateful for this flurry of appreciation. Take part in this wonderful CPA tradition.

You can donate in 2 ways: Go to the PSO website and click on the Snowstorm Link
or send a check/cash to CPA PSO and turn it in to the PSO mailbox in the forum.

Happy Snowstorm!

CALLING ALL SENIOR PARENTS!!

Mrs. Stephens and Mrs. Kurus are the co-coordinators for the Senior Trip 2019. We are excited to co-lead this experience, as it is a trip we have both attended and loved in past years. Seeing the D.C. historic sights and museums together is a beautiful culmination of all of the years of work in the Chandler Prep curriculum, and we can't wait to share it with this great group of students. Please work on the steps below and e-mail us with any questions- bstephens@chandlerprep.org and mkurus@chandlerprep.org.

. **** Sept. 22: $300 due

Chandler Prep Senior Justin Fink has been recognized as a finalist for the prestigious AIA Scholar Activity/Athlete of the Year Award for 2017-18.

Fink will be honored, and the winner will be announced, at the AIA Champions Awards Luncheon to be held on May 21st, 2018 at the University of Phoenix Stadium. The event will be streamed live on http://AZPreps365.com

Justin was selected as a finalist based on the incredibly well rounded resume he has put together in his years spent at Chandler Prep.
